  "texts": [
    "This paradigm not only trains the classification of foreground activities, but also considers background clips and global video information to improve time sensitivity.",
    "As large video datasets with time boundary annotations are difficult to collect, Xu et al. (2021a) designed the boundary-sensitive pretext (BSP) in 2021.",
    "They propose to transform the existing action classification dataset of clip videos to synthesize large-scale untrimmed videos with time boundary annotations.",
    "Specifically, they generate artificial time boundaries that are relatively consistent with changes in video content by splicing clips containing different classes, splicing two video lines of the same class, or manipulating the speed of different parts of the video instance.",
    "Xu et al. (2021b) proposed a simple and limited low-fidelity (LoFi) video encoder optimization method in the same year."
  ],
